<br>
Other than that, I think they did a great job with Luclin, and I'm generally happy.<br>
<br>
For those of you not familiar with the focus item and caster balancing issues...<br>
<br>
1.  Every expansion thus far has had better and better equipment for melees that significantly increases their DPS, DPM, and DPH...higher damage, lower delay.  Also, many many more hps, ac, etc.<br>
<br>
2.  Casters have only very insignificantly changed their DPS, DPM and DPH since day one of EQ, and this primarily through FT items that allow them to med a little faster.  No matter how much mana we have, or what our int is, our DD spells still do the same amount of damage they always have, with just the same cast times.<br>
<br>
3.  This has created a significant disparity between the nuking classes and the melee classes...they have become much much more effecive while we've remained stagnant.<br>
<br>
4.  About six months ago, VI promised that it was working on balancing casters, similar to the melee balance that was done (which I think they did an extremely good job with).  Some time between then and Luclin launch, they said that &quot;Luclin will be the expansion that the casters have been waiting for...&quot;.  Focus items for casters were discussed, and we were told they would be in Luclin.  Items such as 10% increase to damage on Fire based DD spells, 15% on Magic based, etc etc.<br>
<br>
5.  Obviously, none of this materialized...<br>
<br>
<br>
